Java remove character from string

In java, String class do not have remove() method. Meanwhile String class have replace() method with overloaded variations like this as shown below.

replace(char oldChar, char newChar)
replace(CharSequence target, CharSequence replacement)
replaceFirst(String regex, String replacement)
replaceAll(String regex, String replacement)

For more refer this resource - https://www.flowerbrackets.com/java-remove-character-from-string/
